'Vandenberg Air Force Base' is a United States Air Force Base, located
approximately northwest of Lompoc, California. It is under the jurisdiction of
the 30th Space Wing, Air Force Space Command (AFSPC).

Vandenberg AFB is a Department of Defense space and missile testing base, with a
mission of placing satellites into polar orbit from the West Coast, using
expendable boosters (Pegasus, Taurus, Minotaur, Atlas V and Delta IV). Wing
personnel also support the Service's LGM-30G Minuteman III Intercontinental
Ballistic Missile Force Development Evaluation program.

The base is named in honor of former Air Force Chief of Staff General Hoyt S.
Vandenberg.
